A chieftain of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Mr. Godwin Ezeemo, has stressed the need for a purposeful leader to succeed Governor Willie Obiano of Anambra State come 2021. In an interview in Awka, Anambra State capital, he said if a leader with purpose and great ideas emerged as the state governor come 2021, the state economy would bounce back diversified and jobs would be created for the youth. He stated that over 90 percent of Anambra people are jobless because of poor leadership, lack of vision and purposeful leader to take the state to the next level. He said currently, the state is suffering from high rate of unemployment and the only way to solve that was by getting a governor with vision and ideas to create jobs for the teaming youths. He called on Ndi Anambra to come together and work towards restoring the economy of the state by voting somebody who will change and drive the fortune of the state to greater glory. Anambra 2021: Transcorp President, Ozigbo joins guber race Atiku picks Peter Obi as running mate Anambra 2021:Â  Start your political activities now, PDP chair tells aspirants